PROBLEM AND ITS BACKGROUND 



1.1 Introduction 
<General Problem> 
	The difficulty of individuals maintaining their healthy food intake and monitoring their energy levels in the modern world.There is a specific requirement for energy intake that an individual’s body needs in order for it to function properly and to ensure their physiological growth and prevent any diseases that they may encounter. However, many people struggle to track their own macronutrients - carbohydrates, lipids, and proteins, which are essential for primary energy production and bodily functions.
<Specific Problem> 
	Manual tracking limitations are one of the problems that we researchers observed. With this, individuals lack the ability to record their meals and log their daily physical activities. Another limitation is that there is a need for personalized health journeys that calculate the person’s BMI (Body Mass Index) in order to provide a suggestion/s on what meals and physical activities that they should perform daily.

