1.2 The Project 
<Discuss how the project works THOROUGHLY> 
The MacroTracker is a command-line health monitoring system that tracks an individual's daily macronutrient intake. The system allows user's to log meals, record physical activities, and monitor their nutrient intake accurately. The system also computes the user's Body-Mass Index (BMI) to help generate a personalized diet and exercise recommendations.
The system has user authentication feautres, including sign up and log in to ensure security. An admin log in is also available to keep sensitive system operations. 
Overall, MacroTracker serves as a tool that supports the users to make informed decisions about their health and nutrition.

1.3 Objectives 
<General Objectives> 
To create a Command Line Interface system that can track macronutrient intake, compute BMI, and provide personalize diet and exercise recommendations.

1. Develop a CLI system using Python
2. Create a sign up option for new users
3. Implement a user log in to access personalized data
4. Implement admin log in with password to protect sensitive data
5. Compute Body Mass Index (BMI)
6. Track users macronutrient intake and physical activities
7. Automate diet and exercise recommendations based on computed BMI

